 # Int1 underflow tests

(tx 'create schema test')
(tx 'create table test.item(field: int1)')
!tx 'insert (-129) into test.item (field)'
---
> error[PO0002]: value underflows column `field` type `INT1`
>   1 │ insert (-129) into test.item (field)
>     │         ^
>     = value `-129` does not fit into `INT1` (range: -128 to 127)
> 
> note: column `field` is of type `INT1`
> 
> help: increase the value, change the column type to a wider type or change the underflow policy
